<tr>
<td>
<blockquote>
&ldquo;Very accommodating when requesting where to sit as long as there is space available. This visit was during the week and between the business lunch time. Didn’t wait long for the waitress/waiter to arrive at the table. Remember to ask for your free wine tasting (2). Took our order. Everything was tasty and fine with regards to temperature. Portion size was just enough for price paid. With our meal you get a choice of unlimited soup or salad. My advice is for each person to order something different and share. Will definitely return.&rdquo; <br>
- Robert
</blockquote>
</td>
<td>
<blockquote>
&ldquo;Fourteenth of us arrived unexpected, got seated right away, everybody chose the buffet, no complaints at all from the soups to the salads, to the sushi, to the main dishes and of course the desserts, great service, the seniors got there discounts and all in all we where one happy crowd. My Family celebrated a birthday and there was something for everyone. Our server went above and beyond to make it fun and memorable &rdquo;<br>
- John
</blockquote>
</td>
<td>
<blockquote>
&ldquo;Typical Five Guys fare in a spacious and well lit setting. All burgers are good (we had 4 types). Fries are excellent and plentiful. Don't forget the free peanuts. Notable that this location serves delicious milkshakes! Excellent service, a bit pricey but well worth it for the incredible fry’s and burgers. Everyone’s always friendly and you feel at home right away. We will definitely return A+++ &rdquo;<br>
- Jackson
</blockquote>
</td>
